#!/bin/bash
# SubagentStart hook — injects rules into subagent context

cat <<'EOF'
{"additionalContext": "## Injected Rules for Subagents\n\n### Import Boundaries\n- apps/{a}/ CANNOT import from apps/{b}/ -- use shared components instead\n- modules/{a}/ CANNOT import from modules/{b}/ -- use lib/\n- components/ui/ CANNOT import from apps/ or platform/\n- Shared components: components/ui/ (primitives), components/patterns/ (reusable patterns)\n\n### Tenant Isolation (CRITICAL)\n- Every DB query MUST filter by tenantId\n- Services receive tenantId as a parameter, never access Hono context\n- Every module MUST have a tenant isolation test\n\n### Architecture\n- Backend modules: routes.ts -> service.ts -> schema.ts (never skip a layer)\n- Frontend apps: register via registry.ts, lazy-load routes\n- Design tokens: use CSS custom properties, never hardcode colors\n\n### Testing Depth (CRITICAL)\n- L1 (Unit): business logic, service functions -> unit tests with concrete values\n- L2 (Integration): UI/backend wiring -> test clicks trigger correct API calls\n- L3 (Behavioral): user flows -> verify interactions produce results in browser\n- L4 (Output): features producing artifacts -> verify content correctness\n- 'Visible in snapshot' != 'working'. A button appearing but doing nothing = FAIL.\n- Run only YOUR module tests: npm run test --workspace=packages/web -- src/apps/{name}/\n- Do NOT run the full test suite -- that's the lead's job\n\n### Ports\n- API: http://localhost:3001\n- Web: http://localhost:5173\n\n### Tech Conventions\n- TypeScript strict, no `any`, named exports, ESM only\n- Shell: Windows MINGW64, use `python` not `python3`\n- Use `node -e` for JSON parsing (jq may not be available)"}
EOF
